kiwicraft
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:the rolling of fleece wool between hand and thigh to produce a strand for knitting, a practice of older Maori women in woolsheds.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See: uruapihi; warahipi
